{"aid": "http://arxiv.org/abs/2504.05872v1", "title": "On free line arrangements with double, triple and quadruple points", "summary": "We show that there are only finitely many combinatorial types of free real
line arrangements with only double, triple and quadruple intersection points,
and we enlist all admissible weak-combinatorics of them. Then we classify all
real $M$-line arrangements. In particular, we show that real $M$-line
arrangements are simplicial.", "main_category": "math.AG", "categories": "math.AG,math.CO", "published": "2025-04-08T09:56:51Z"}
